        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 3:39PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 339 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northwest of Shelby, or near Kingstown. This storm was nearly
stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lawndale, Lattimore, Mooresboro, Kingstown, and Ellenboro.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
